OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FShowers
OL,6,Fmostly dying out this evening with
OL,7,Flate sunny intervals. A dry start
OL,8,Ftonight then cloud thickening to bring
OL,9,Foutbreaks of rain from the early hours.
OL,10,
OL,11,CMonday:FA cloudy day with outbreaks of
OL,12,Frain, this turning heavy at times. A
OL,13,Ffew limited brighter intervals in east
OL,14,Flater, where it could be quite warm.
OL,15,FMore showery in evening.
OL,16,
OL,17,COutlook for Tuesday to Thursday:FBright
OL,18,Fspells and some heavy showers Tuesday.
OL,19,FDry start Wednesday then some showers.
OL,20,FMostly cloudy with showers on
OL,21,FThursday, and quite breezy.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
